!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

bold /bəʊld/

(bolder,boldest) 

1. ADJ Someone who is bold is not afraid to do things that involve risk or danger. 无畏的; 大胆的 

例： Amrita becomes a bold, daring rebel. 阿莫瑞塔成了一位英勇无畏的反叛者。 

例： In 1960 this was a bold move. 在1960年，这是一个大胆的举动。 

2. boldly ADV 无畏地; 大胆地 [ADV with v] 

例： You must act boldly and confidently. 你必须表现得大胆、自信。 

3. ADJ Someone who is bold is not shy or embarrassed in the company of other people. 大胆的 

例： I don't feel I'm being bold, because it's always been natural for me to just speak out about whatever disturbs me. 我并不认为自己莽撞，因为无论什么事令我不安我就说出来，对我这一直以来是很自然的事。 

4. boldly ADV 大胆地 

例： 'You should do it,' the girl said, boldly. 这个女孩大胆地说道：“你应该这么做。” 

5. ADJ A bold colour or pattern is very bright and noticeable. (色彩或图案) 鲜明的; 醒目的 

例： ...bold flowers in various shades of red, blue or white. …各种深浅不同的红色、蓝色和白色的醒目的花朵。 

6. ADJ Bold lines or designs are drawn in a clear, strong way. 清晰的; (线条、轮廓) 刚劲的; 大胆的 

例： Each picture is shown in colour on one page and as a bold outline on the opposite page. 每幅画在一页上是彩色的，在相对的一页上则是清晰刚劲的轮廓。 

7. N-UNCOUNT Bold is print which is thicker and looks blacker than ordinary printed letters. 粗体 [技术] 

例： When a candidate is elected his or her name will be highlighted in bold. 当候选人被选中时，他或她的名字就用粗体来突出。

